The new management of the Nigeria Social Insurance Trust Fund (NSITF) led by the Acting Managing Director (MD), Kelly Nwagha, has promised financial prudence while targeting an increase in the number of enrollees to the scheme. The new management team appealed to workers of the organisation for support, noting that the success of the management would determine the level of trust the Federal Government would repose on the ability of staff members to navigate the ship of the Fund going forward. Nwagha stated this while addressing workers of the agency at the end of their inauguration at the headquarters of the Fund in Abuja, adding that their appointments is at the request of President Muhammadu Buhari. 